text: Larisa Kuzhugetovna Shoygu (, 21 January 1953 â€“ 10 June 2021) was a Russian politician. She was a Deputy of the State Duma from 2007 until her death. She was a member of United Russia. Shoygu was born in Chadan, Soviet Union. Shoygu died on 10 June 2021, at a hospital in Moscow from a stroke caused by COVID-19, aged 68. ==References== Category:1953 births Category:2021 deaths Category:Members of the State Duma Category:Deaths from the COVID-19 pandemic in Moscow Category:Psychiatrists
